  <abstract>Item consists of a recording of a workshop focusing on Boogies, Foxtrots and Two Steps, hosted by Ken Whiteley.  Beginning with a a piano solo of "Coquette" aka "Little Coquette" (Guy Lombardo?) followed by John Davis performing "Kansas City" (Jerry Leiber Mike Stoller) followed by the Original Sloth Band performing "Honeysuckle Rose" (Andy Razaf (lyrics), Fats Waller). The recording cuts off mid-song.</abstract>
